      <h2>Why a popup is not a break</h2>
      <p>
        Every trader who has tilted knows the move: the warning dialog appears, the hand clicks it away, the next order goes in. The whole problem with tilt is that the person at the keyboard in that moment is not the person who set the rule. A lockout that can be dismissed by the tilted version of you is not a lockout — it's a speed bump.
      </p>
      <p>
        That is the design brief behind the Cool-down Wall, tier 5 of Guard v2's six-tier ladder: the break has to actually happen.
      </p>

      <h2>What the Cool-down Wall does</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Covers the whole screen.</strong> Not a dialog — a full-screen takeover with your rule's name, a countdown, and nothing to trade on.</li>
        <li><strong>Guides the break.</strong> A breathing pacer (in for four seconds, out for six) and occasional calm one-liners. The wall isn't a punishment screen; it's a structured cool-down, closer to a meditation timer than to a lock screen.</li>
        <li><strong>Never traps an open position.</strong> If you hold a position when the rule fires, a small dialog comes first: close it for me, or I'll close it myself. The wall only takes over once you are verifiably flat — and closing or reducing a position is never blocked, at any tier.</li>
        <li><strong>Soft or hard — your call, made in advance.</strong> The soft wall can be Alt-Tabbed for emergencies. The hard wall re-asserts focus until the timer releases you. You pick per rule, while calm.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>When even a wall isn't enough</h2>
      <p>
        Above the wall sits tier 6, <strong>Cut</strong>: a Windows-firewall block of your broker's order servers, so an order physically cannot leave the PC — the one stop that holds even a market order on a prop account. See <a href="/answers/can-trading-software-block-me-from-placing-orders" class="text-emerald-700 underline">can trading software block me from placing orders?</a> for how that works.
      </p>

      <h2>And on NinjaTrader 8?</h2>
      <p>
        The NinjaTrader 8 add-on (GA) escalates through five levels — Notify, Risk Alert, Acknowledge, Trading Pause, and a full broker Disconnect — with the same philosophy: you write the rule calm, Guard enforces it tilted, and an un-bypassable <a href="/guard" class="text-emerald-700 underline">Strict Lock</a> can make every pause absolute for its full window. The Cool-down Wall and Cut are part of Guard v2, first on the standalone apps.
      </p>

      <p>
        Full model: <a href="/guard#guard-v2" class="text-emerald-700 underline">Meridian Guard — the escalation ladders</a>. Platform availability: <a href="/platforms" class="text-emerald-700 underline">capability matrix</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

